<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-50-0003 </DOCNO><TEXT>Perfusion scintigraphy of the testicles has still its place, in additionto scrotal ultrasound imaging, in the investigation of the 'acute scrotum'.It reveals scintigraphic patterns typical for twisted testicle and acuteor subacute epididymitis. Especially in the Bundeswehr, with its largenumber of young men, this method enhances the diagnostic spectrum andhelps in making surgical decisions. However, in the examination of scrotalmasses, ultrasound imaging or surgery is to be preferred.</TEXT></DOC>